A lil’ #bestof2022 tattoo therapy love 🤧
•
Y’all! Transparnecy with your customers is everything! Wins EVERY time …

I had a panic attack literally moments before our tattoo session. It went something like ~

Just so you know I’m trying to curb a panic attack so we can tattoo (something financial touched my soul and welp financial trauma was triggered 😳)

He calmly said Ok. No problem.

I failed at curbing it and was on my say to run to the bathroom and it was worse than anybody’s I pooped my pants moment 😅

Only a few seconda after crossing the threahold, exiting my studio, I fell to the floor. I remember a buz neighbor helping me and when I returned I was mute ~

I often lose my voice in panic attacks.

So I played it like I was one of my deaf customers and got an envelope. I told him I’m fine to tattoo but no coice. And asked him to trust me. I know thas a tall order but …

Turned out to be one of THE BEST SESSIONS

And that envelope … we still have it 🤧😅✨

Yesterday’s impromptu Ink & Release meetings were so deliciously overwhelming I had to legit take a nao to swerve mania right fast 🤧
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I started talking Tattoo Therapy and tattoo being more than a tattoo well before 2019. But really started deep diving then ~
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But because my oversized vision of what I see myself bringing forth was so engulfing that it overwhelmed me, I ran. I played small and I tried to wholly neglect my purpose and calling in this space - even despite actively practicing tattoo therapy everyday.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was scared to say I practice ancestral veneration with every tattoo. That I’m not for everybody. And that I also consult with your ancestors when designing a tattoo.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I mean, how do you explain being a mystic. An oracle  or psychic of sorts when you don’t understand it yourself?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So that’s what I been doing all 2022.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Instead of consulting ancestors on my clients’ behalves, I had to turn inward and consult them for me. For this journey ~
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For FULLY EMBRACING + defining tattoo therapy
for Black culture, accepting the vision as it was given to me, and trusting the process.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
They say when you want something the ENTIRE universe conspires in your favor. And it’s not that I never wanted it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I was just scared of my own voice. 
My own power. But …
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2023, I WILL DO MY BEST!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Spend a day with me - a tattoo therapist. Today WE OUTSIDE on a creative community care play date ~

1. supporting an @lipsbrand.online client - who needed a moment with his inner child

2. supporting my apprentice - who deserved a moment of celebration for her tattoo rite of passage
